The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Mohammedan Sporting have demanded a public apology from Mohun Bagan secretary Anjan Mitra for his comment that the name of the club was communal in nature in todays context. In a letter to Mitra, Mohammedan Sporting secretary Sultan Ahmed said his comments were a matter of great shame and insult to the club.                
	 Ajgar Ali and Somdeb Chanda emerged champions in the four-wheeler category of 10th Kaviguru Rally from Calcutta to Shantiniketan, organised by Bengal Motor Sports Club on Saturday. In the two wheeler section, the team of Subhamoy Paul and Rajdip Fadikar won.          
	 Micah Muhury and Aandrita Deb entered the final of the ladies open singles at the Calcutta Hardcourt Tennis Championship. Micah defeated Ishani Mukherjee 6-2, 6-0 while Aandrita beat Andrea Das 6-1, 6-1. In the mens open singles Saurav Panja ousted fourth seed Robin Das 6-1, 6-3. Manoj Kumar Sewa, Vinod Kumar Sewa and Harshvardhan Thirani also made it to the semis.          
	TENNIS: Calcutta Hardcourt at South Club from noon.                                                                                                                                                                     
